		<summary type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/116-nigel-brown&quot;&gt;Nigel Brown&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/181-narrative-techniques-and-the-night-land&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/fabian-redoubt-green-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;An armed man outside a tall, steep-sided pyramid, surrounded by green mist&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;... the power of Hodgson's novel goes beyond that conjured up by his imagination. Hodgson uses solid narrative techniques to tell his story; techniques which are worth a closer look by any writer interested in writing a gripping story.&lt;/p&gt;
